                        <provenance>     
                            <persName role="owner" ref="">Walda Kidān Yǝmanu</persName> is mentioned in several supplication formulas throughout the manuscript: 
                            he possibly was the original owner of the book.
                            According to the account on the manuscripts’ provenance given by Tisserant, this manuscript is among those acquired by 
                            <persName ref="PRS4805Grebaut" role="owner"/> in <placeName ref="LOC1216AddisA">ʾAddis ʾAbabā</placeName> in <date when="1925"/> with funds of
                            <persName ref="PRS14055SaintJ">Jean Saint</persName>. 
                            The manuscripts originated from Šawā (ʾAddis ʾAbabā, Dabra Libānos, Dabra Bǝrhān), Goǧǧām (Dimā Giyorgis, Marṭula Māryām, Dabra Warq) and Bagemdǝr
                            (Gondar, ʾAzazo Takla Hāymānot) and very few from Tǝgrāy.
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition when="1928">The manuscript entered the library on <date when="1928-04-18">18 April 1928</date>.</acquisition>
                    </history>
                    
